#: ../../nextcloud.rst:21
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:23
msgid ""
"Nextcloud needs a dedicated virtual host, a FQDN like "
"``nextcloud.nethserver.org``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:25
msgid ""
"Before proceeding with the configuration, make sure to create the "
"corresponding name record inside your DNS server. If you are planning to "
"use a Let's Encrypt certificate as default, make also sure to have a "
"corresponding public DNS record."
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:28
msgid "After the installation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:30
msgid "access the ``Settings`` page of the newly installed instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:31
msgid "enter a valid FQDN inside the ``Host name`` field"
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:32
msgid "enable ``Let's Encrypt`` option accordingly to your needs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:33
msgid "click the :guilabel:`Save` button"
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:35
msgid ""
"Then click on ``Configure Nextcloud`` to run the first configuration "
"wizard. The wizard will ask to setup an administrator user and password. "
"If during the wizard you are going to install recommended apps, please "
"note that the built-in Collabora server (Nextcloud Office) will not work."
" If you want to integrate with Collabora online see :ref:`below "
"<collabora-integration-section>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:40
msgid ""
"After the wizard has been completed, return to the NethServer page and "
"reload it. You can now connect Nextcloud to an existing :ref:`user domain"
" <user-domains-section>` by selecting the domain under the ``User "
"domain`` field. All users configured inside the domain will be able to "
"access the Nextcloud installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:44
msgid ""
"Nextcloud update/upgrade procedure may disables the apps to avoid "
"incompatibility problems. Server logs keep track of which apps were "
"disabled. After a successful update/upgrade procedure you can use the "
"Applications page to update and re-enable the apps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:49
msgid "User list"
msgstr ""

#: ../../nextcloud.rst:51
msgid ""
"All users are listed inside the administrator panel of Nextcloud using a "
"unique identifier containing letters and numbers. This is because the "
"system ensures that there are no duplicate internal user names as "
"reported in section `Internal Username` of `Official Nextcloud "
"documentation <https://docs.nextcloud.com>`_."
msgstr ""

